<item>
            <title>[LU-4783] start params llog automatically during mgs setup</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4783</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Params llog was introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3155&quot; title=&quot;Permanent parameters with lctl set_param -P&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3155&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3155&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to use &quot;lctl set_param -P&quot; to set parameters permanently instead of &quot;lctl conf_param&quot;. But during investigation on &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3410&quot; title=&quot;mgc_copy_llog()) Failed to copy remote log routed1-OST00b3 (-2) ecountered during bring up of a 2.4 file system&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3410&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3410&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; I find that when a new filesystem is mounted, params llog won&apos;t be created automatically until &quot;set_param -P&quot; is called. So before running &quot;set_param -P&quot;, there is no params llog in mgs and the other servers can&apos;t make a local copy successfully.&lt;br/&gt;
This causes the console error message &quot;LustreError: 13a-8: Failed to get MGS log params and no local copy.&quot;is printed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will push a patch later.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
